actions.comment:
Thanks for the detailed report and benchmarks!

**Immediate workaround — cache `SKTextBlob` instances:**

The `DrawText(string, ...)` overload currently creates a new `SKTextBlob` on every call, which incurs text layout overhead each frame. Caching blobs gives a reported 5–7x speedup:

```csharp
// One-time setup per screen/component:
var _textBlobCache = new Dictionary<string, SKTextBlob?>();

// Per-frame drawing (fast path):
if (!_textBlobCache.TryGetValue(label, out var blob))
{
    blob = SKTextBlob.Create(label, font);
    _textBlobCache[label] = blob;
}
if (blob != null)
    canvas.DrawText(blob, x, y, paint);

// Cleanup when done:
foreach (var b in _textBlobCache.Values) b?.Dispose();
_textBlobCache.Clear();
```

**Note:** If your font or text size changes, invalidate the cached blob for that key.

We're also tracking a deeper GL rendering regression from the 2.80.x era — the raw per-call cost has grown roughly 3–4x on Android/GL from version 1.68.3 to 3.x. The 3.119.0 release brought improvements on Windows but Android hasn't seen the same gains yet.
